A split composition in Studio Ghibli style: on one side, a humble scientist in a modest laboratory surrounded by glowing vials and botanical specimens, sunlight streaming through dusty windows, delicate herbs hanging from the ceiling; on the other side, a prosperous businessman standing atop industrial pipes and machinery processing murky water into crystal clear streams, golden coins flowing alongside the purified water. Both figures rendered with warm, expressive features and soft watercolor textures. The scene bathed in that distinctive Ghibli golden-hour lighting, with whimsical clouds connecting both halves of the image, suggesting the philosophical weight of the comparison between noble purpose and profitable pragmatism.
